    <p><strong>Commercial popcorn machine prices in India in 2026 range from ₹5,000 for a basic countertop electric model to over ₹1,50,000 for a high-output gas popcorn machine with a warming showcase and mobile cart. Cotton candy machine prices in India start at ₹4,000 for a manual tabletop unit and go up to ₹80,000 for a fully automatic commercial cotton candy machine with output exceeding 10 kg per hour.</strong> Whether you're setting up a cinema snack counter, a carnival stall, a mall kiosk, or a mobile food cart, this comprehensive guide covers every type, price point, brand, and business consideration you need to choose the right popcorn and cotton candy machine for your requirements.</p>

    <p>Popcorn and cotton candy (buddhi ke baal) are two of India's highest-margin snack businesses. A popcorn stall at a busy market can generate ₹5,000–₹15,000 in daily revenue with profit margins of 60–75%, while cotton candy stalls at fairs and carnivals routinely earn ₹3,000–₹8,000 per day with margins exceeding 80%. The best part? Both businesses require minimal equipment, low raw material costs, and very little skill to operate. But your profitability starts with buying the right machine at the right price.</p>

