    <h2>Types of Commercial Popcorn Machines in India</h2>
    <p>Popcorn machines available in India fall into several categories depending on fuel type, form factor, and the type of popcorn they produce. Let's break down each type in detail to help you find the right commercial popcorn machine for your business.</p>

    <h3>1. Electric Countertop Popcorn Machine</h3>
    <p>The electric countertop popcorn machine is the most common type used in cinemas, retail shops, and small snack counters across India. It features a heated kettle (usually aluminium or stainless steel) mounted inside a transparent glass or acrylic cabinet that doubles as a display case. The kettle pops corn using an electric heating element, and the popped kernels fall into the cabinet where they stay warm under a heat lamp.</p>

    <p><strong>Key specifications:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Kettle capacity:</strong> 100g–500g per batch (small: 100–200g, commercial: 300–500g)</li>
      <li><strong>Power consumption:</strong> 800W–2500W depending on kettle size</li>
      <li><strong>Cabinet material:</strong> Tempered glass panels with SS or powder-coated steel frame</li>
      <li><strong>Kettle material:</strong> Aluminium (budget) or stainless steel (recommended for commercial use)</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 2–5 kg of popped corn per hour (a 300g kettle yields roughly 8–10 litres per batch)</li>
      <li><strong>Warm holding capacity:</strong> 20–50 litres in the display cabinet</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Clean, professional look — the glass cabinet doubles as a display that attracts customers</li>
      <li>Easy to operate — just add oil, kernels, and salt/butter, then switch on</li>
      <li>Available in a wide price range (₹5,000–₹25,000) to suit any budget</li>
      <li>Compact footprint — fits on a standard countertop</li>
      <li>No gas cylinder needed — safer for indoor operation in malls and cinemas</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Requires stable electricity — not ideal for areas with frequent power cuts unless you have backup</li>
      <li>Lower output compared to gas machines at the same price point</li>
      <li>Higher electricity costs for continuous operation (₹100–₹300/day depending on usage)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Cinema halls, mall food courts, restaurant snack counters, retail shops, offices, and any indoor location with reliable power. This is the best choice for most businesses looking for a commercial popcorn machine in India.</p>

    <h3>2. Gas-Operated Commercial Popcorn Machine</h3>
    <p>Gas popcorn machines use LPG gas as the heat source, which makes them popular for outdoor stalls, mobile carts, events, and locations without reliable electricity. The gas burner heats a large kettle (typically SS 304 or heavy-gauge aluminium), and the operator manually stirs or shakes the kernels to ensure even popping. Higher-end models feature a motorized stirring mechanism.</p>

    <p><strong>Key specifications:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Kettle capacity:</strong> 300g–1 kg per batch</li>
      <li><strong>Gas consumption:</strong> 200–400g LPG per hour of continuous operation</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 4–10 kg of popped corn per hour</li>
      <li><strong>Kettle material:</strong> SS 304 (commercial grade) or aluminium (budget)</li>
      <li><strong>Frame/body:</strong> Stainless steel or painted mild steel</li>
    </ul>

