    </ul>

    <p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Gas cylinder handling and storage requires care, especially in enclosed spaces</li>
      <li>Some malls and cinemas do not allow open-flame equipment indoors</li>
      <li>Requires more operator attention — not as "set and forget" as electric models</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Outdoor events, carnivals, fairs, mobile carts, roadside stalls, and any location where electricity is unavailable or unreliable.</p>

    <h3>3. Popcorn Cart with Warming Showcase</h3>
    <p>A complete popcorn cart is a mobile vending unit that includes the popcorn maker (electric or gas), a warming showcase with heat lamps, storage compartments for raw materials, and wheels for mobility. This is the go-to setup for mobile popcorn vendors, mall kiosk operators, and event caterers in India.</p>

    <p><strong>What's typically included:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Popcorn making unit (electric or gas kettle)</li>
      <li>Glass warming showcase (keeps popped corn warm and visible)</li>
      <li>Storage shelf for kernels, oil, butter, and seasoning</li>
      <li>Paper bag/cup holder</li>
      <li>Heavy-duty wheels with brakes</li>
      <li>Canopy or umbrella mount (for outdoor carts)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Price range:</strong> ₹25,000 – ₹60,000 depending on build quality, size, and whether the popper is electric or gas. Custom-built stainless steel carts with branding panels can cost ₹50,000–₹80,000.</p>

    <p><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Mobile popcorn vendors, event caterers, mall kiosk businesses, and anyone who needs a professional, portable setup. If you're also considering display equipment, check our <a href="/blog/display-counter-price-india">display counter price guide</a> for complementary options.</p>

    <h3>4. Caramel, Cheese & Flavoured Popcorn Machine</h3>
    <p>The flavoured popcorn segment is growing rapidly in India, driven by gourmet popcorn brands in malls and online delivery. Making caramel popcorn, cheese popcorn, or other flavoured varieties requires additional equipment beyond a standard popper.</p>

    <p><strong>Equipment needed for flavoured popcorn:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard popcorn maker:</strong> Any electric or gas machine to pop the plain kernels</li>
      <li><strong>Caramel coating machine (candy coating pan):</strong> ₹20,000 – ₹50,000 — a heated rotating drum that evenly coats popcorn with melted caramel, chocolate, or cheese sauce</li>
      <li><strong>Flavouring tumbler:</strong> ₹15,000 – ₹35,000 — for dry seasoning application (cheese powder, masala, peri-peri, etc.)</li>
      <li><strong>Sugar melting unit:</strong> ₹8,000 – ₹15,000 — for caramel preparation</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Total investment for flavoured popcorn setup:</strong> ₹50,000 – ₹1,50,000 depending on the scale and variety of flavours you plan to offer. The profit margins on flavoured popcorn are significantly higher — a ₹10 bag of plain popcorn can become a ₹50–₹100 bag of caramel or cheese popcorn.</p>

