    <ul>
      <li><strong>Starting a small popcorn stall (budget under ₹15,000):</strong> Buy a basic electric countertop popcorn machine (₹8,000–₹12,000). It's sufficient for 50–80 servings per day, looks professional, and requires minimal skill to operate.</li>
      <li><strong>Commercial popcorn business at a market or event (₹20,000–₹50,000):</strong> Invest in a gas-operated popcorn machine with a mobile cart and warming showcase. The gas model gives you location flexibility and higher output. The cart makes you look professional and mobile.</li>
      <li><strong>Cinema or mall popcorn counter (₹50,000–₹1,50,000):</strong> Get 2–3 large electric countertop machines with glass cabinets, plus a caramel coating unit for premium variants. The multi-machine setup handles rush-hour demand without long queues.</li>
      <li><strong>Cotton candy at events and fairs (₹10,000–₹20,000):</strong> A mid-range commercial electric cotton candy machine is all you need. It pays for itself within the first 2–3 events. Pair it with a popcorn machine for a complete snack stall.</li>
      <li><strong>Combo popcorn + cotton candy business (₹30,000–₹60,000):</strong> This is our top recommendation for new entrepreneurs. Both machines together cost less than ₹50,000, offer combined profit potential of ₹50,000–₹75,000 per month, and serve the same customer base. It's one of the lowest-investment, highest-return food businesses you can start in India today.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Whatever machine you choose, prioritise SS 304 construction, buy from a dealer with after-sales service, and always get a live demonstration before paying. If you're planning a larger food business setup alongside popcorn and cotton candy, explore our <a href="/blog/bakery-machine-price-list-india">bakery machine price list</a> and <a href="/blog/commercial-kitchen-equipment-guide">commercial kitchen equipment guide</a> for a complete picture of the equipment landscape in India.</p>

